laboratory_examinations.procedure_name: CT abdomen and pelvis with IV contrast
laboratory_examinations.findings: Extensive fat stranding and fluid within the right lower quadrant. The appendix is dilated and fluid-filled measuring up to 2.2 cm. There is disruption of the appendiceal wall with extraluminal foci of air and a developing fluid collection, which measures approximately 3.7 x 2.5 x 4.9 cm. There is normal liver, pancreas, spleen, adrenal glands, and kidneys. No bowel obstruction.
Positive for Gram positive cocci in clusters.
